\subsection{\href{https://beta.lmfdb.org/knowledge/show/crystals.highest_weight}{Highest weight crystals}}
\begin{definition}\label{crystals.highest_weight}
\uses{crystals.crystal}
Highest weight crystals are \hyperref[crystals.crystal]{Crystal} which have a highest weight element. A highest weight element $b$ is annihilated by all Kashiwara raising operators:
\[
e_i b = 0 \quad \text{for all } i\in I.
\]
The weight of the highest weight element is used to label the crystal.
\end{definition}
